### Solution
This function uses a recursive strategy. The buggy function will calculate how many ways one can make change using the first coin, and then recursively add the number of ways in which the change can be made without the first coin. If this recursive call doesn't change the answer, that means the answer is the same as the number of ways without the first coin. This solution works well because the function is only concerned with the first coin, and any other coin is irrelevant.


